Terminals unused in grammar

   WHILE
   PRINTLN
   DECOP


Grammar

    0 $accept: start $end

    1 start: program

    2 program: program unit
    3        | unit

    4 unit: var_declaration
    5     | func_definition

    6 func_definition: type_specifier ID LPAREN parameter_list RPAREN compound_statement
    7                | type_specifier ID LPAREN RPAREN compound_statement

    8 parameter_list: parameter_list COMMA type_specifier ID
    9               | type_specifier ID

   10 compound_statement: LCURL statements RCURL
   11                   | LCURL RCURL

   12 var_declaration: type_specifier declaration_list SEMICOLON

   13 type_specifier: INT
   14               | FLOAT
   15               | VOID

   16 declaration_list: declaration_list COMMA ID
   17                 | ID

   18 statements: statement
   19           | statements statement

   20 statement: var_declaration
   21          | expression_statement
   22          | compound_statement
   23          | FOR LPAREN expression_statement expression_statement expression RPAREN statement
   24          | IF LPAREN expression RPAREN statement
   25          | IF LPAREN expression RPAREN statement ELSE statement
   26          | RETURN expression SEMICOLON

   27 expression_statement: SEMICOLON
   28                     | expression SEMICOLON

   29 expression: logic_expression
   30           | variable ASSIGNOP logic_expression

   31 logic_expression: rel_expression
   32                 | rel_expression LOGICOP rel_expression

   33 rel_expression: simple_expression
   34               | simple_expression RELOP simple_expression

   35 simple_expression: term
   36                  | simple_expression ADDOP term

   37 term: unary_expression
   38     | term MULOP unary_expression

   39 unary_expression: ADDOP unary_expression
   40                 | NOT unary_expression
   41                 | factor

   42 factor: variable
   43       | ID LPAREN argument_list RPAREN
   44       | LPAREN expression RPAREN
   45       | CONST_INT
   46       | CONST_FLOAT
   47       | variable INCOP

   48 variable: ID
   49         | ID LTHIRD expression RTHIRD

   50 argument_list: arguments
   51              | /* empty */

   52 arguments: arguments COMMA logic_expression
   53          | logic_expression


